<li id="cite_note-atheists-50"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">‚Üë <sup><a href="#cite_ref-atheists_50-0">47.0</a></sup> <sup><a href="#cite_ref-atheists_50-1">47.1</a></sup></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r9435658"><cite id="CITEREFSpeciale2013" class="citation news cs1">Speciale, Alessandro (20 March 2013). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20130621220805/http://articles.washingtonpost.com/2013-03-20/national/37864118_1_atheists-and-believers-spiritual-leader-muslim-leaders">"Pope Francis says atheists can be 'allies' for the church"</a>. <i>Washington Post</i>. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://articles.washingtonpost.com/2013-03-20/national/37864118_1_atheists-and-believers-spiritual-leader-muslim-leaders">the original</a> on 21 June 2013<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2 March</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Washington+Post&amp;rft.atitle=Pope+Francis+says+atheists+can+be+%27allies%27+for+the+church&amp;rft.date=2013-03-20&amp;rft.aulast=Speciale&amp;rft.aufirst=Alessandro&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farticles.washingtonpost.com%2F2013-03-20%2Fnational%2F37864118_1_atheists-and-believers-spiritual-leader-muslim-leaders&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fsimple.wikipedia.org%3APope+Francis" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-51"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><a href="#cite_ref-51">‚Üë</a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r9435658"><cite id="CITEREFDay2013" class="citation news cs1">Day, Michael (11 September 2013). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20150925191341/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/pope-francis-assures-atheists-you-dont-have-to-believe-in-god-to-go-to-heaven-8810062.html">"Pope Francis assures atheists: You don't have to believe in God to go to heaven"</a>. <i>The Independent</i>. London. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/pope-francis-assures-atheists-you-dont-have-to-believe-in-god-to-go-to-heaven-8810062.html">the original</a> on 25 September 2015<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2 March</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Independent&amp;rft.atitle=Pope+Francis+assures+atheists%3A+You+don%27t+have+to+believe+in+God+to+go+to+heaven&amp;rft.date=2013-09-11&amp;rft.aulast=Day&amp;rft.aufirst=Michael&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.independent.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fpope-francis-assures-atheists-you-dont-have-to-believe-in-god-to-go-to-heaven-8810062.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fsimple.wikipedia.org%3APope+Francis" class="Z3988"></span></span>
