<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r8087918"><div class="reflist reflist-lower-alpha">
<div class="mw-references-wrap"><ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-2"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><a href="#cite_ref-2">‚Üë</a></span> <span class="reference-text">Press reports have provided a variety of translations for the phrase. According to <a href="/wiki/Vatican_Radio" title="Vatican Radio">Vatican Radio</a>: "Pope Francis has chosen the motto <i>Miserando atque eligendo</i>, meaning lowly but chosen; literally in Latin by having mercy, by choosing him. The motto is one Francis used as bishop. It is taken from the homilies of the <a href="/wiki/Bede" title="Bede">Venerable Bede</a> on <a href="/wiki/Gospel_of_Matthew" title="Gospel of Matthew">Saint Matthew's Gospel</a> relating to his vocation: 'Jesus saw the tax collector and by having mercy chose him as an apostle saying to him: Follow me.'"<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-34"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><a href="#cite_ref-34">‚Üë</a></span> <span class="reference-text">Both in the <a href="/wiki/Eastern_Catholic_Churches" class="mw-redirect" title="Eastern Catholic Churches">Eastern Catholic Churches</a> and in the <a href="/w/index.php?title=Eastern_Orthodox_Churches&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Eastern Orthodox Churches (not yet started)">Eastern Orthodox Churches</a>, married men can be ordained to the priesthood, but priests cannot marry after having been ordained. See <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.vatican.va/holy_father/john_paul_ii/apost_constitutions/documents/hf_jp-ii_apc_19901018_codex-can-eccl-orient-2_lt.html#TITULUS_XVI">Code of Canons of the Eastern Churches, canon 795</a></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-44"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><a href="#cite_ref-44">‚Üë</a></span> <span class="reference-text"> One priest was suspended after refusing his bishop's order to cease his advocacy.<sup id="cite_ref-43" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-43">&#91;41&#93;</a></sup></span>
</li>
</ol></div></div>
